< text>
Brand new Whole Foods Market located in downtown Sunnyvale. Ample parking, short lines, never out of stock items, and friendly staff. Located in downtown Sunnyvale near Target, restaurants and bars, and El Camino Real.This store has many special features - lines are short and it's located in a great spot.

[The Features]
A full beer bar with seating, a sushi table, a deli, meat and seafood, produce department, and many grocery items including beer, wine, and spirits.

[Welcome Addition]
The parking here is one of the best parts. They have a dedicated parking lot just for the store. You can bring your carts to the lot and there is an escalator that brings the carts down.

The staff here is also great. They have many cash registers and the lines are managed well. We never have to wait more than a minute or two. This is one of our new favorite spots for going grocery shopping!<//text>

<Name>M B</Name>< review>
Very neat, clever usage of fridge space, like the shelves for small items like spices and chocolates, the chilled drinks are all placed in one section unlike Los Altos, appreciate the team member picks, lots of hot food options and fancy cakes. Unfortunately they don't have ground chicken other than prepackaged.
As someone else mentioned, there were no recycle or compost bins and had to give my personal details to sit down outside. It was apparently for COVID related policy.<//review>

<UserId.>107069339132307105014</UserId.><username>Christopher Schoppet-Panzarini</username><date>1604111812562<//date><rating>4</rating><review>Had a wonderful, if slightly overwhelming, experience at the brand-new, much anticipated Whole Foods Market today.

It was an adventure exploring the enormous store! I was most excited about their huge selection of beers, wines, cheeses, produce, seafood, and meat.

They have a huge beer selection, full of local brews and mainly full of IPAs and Stouts, for the most part (not complaining because that's mainly what I drink). Would have loved more organization of what is from where and what kind of beer they are.

I had to ask for help finding things, especially since the store is so new and so large, and I didn't know my way around just yet. The employees were super friendly and helpful though. I was asked if I needed help many times when I didn't and when I did they showed and guided me to what's on sale and what's a good deal, not just the priciest item on the shelf.

Recommendations: Park in the parking structure and enter from there if you're grocery shopping, park across the street in the Macy's lot of you're going for Floodcraft Brews (beer, food, coffee) or Whole Food's cooked to order section, which includes rice bowls, soups, sandwiches, sushi, and charcuterie too (though the cheese is opposite the meats on the other side of the store, fyi, by the wines and beers).

Also, bring hand sanitizer, many packages in house products had the labels on the bottom requiring picking them up, handling them, and checking the label to see what it is or what's in it. In COVID times, this makes me cringe, but, it looks nicer, I get that...

Glad this was finished and is so close to downtown Sunnyvale. Excited to learn its secrets, best foods, and enjoy this newly minted cornucopia.</review>< pics>

< rate>

<review>Great staff and your average selection of off the shelf auto parts for most major makes and models.

If you've got a question or are unsure where to find something, asking a staff member always helps, as opposed to aimlessly wandering the aisles.

Minor criticism would be the air filter selection. Brands were limited, and the shelves didn't appear to be stocked in a consistent order (e.g. they appeared to be stocked by part number, but probably only 70% of the time).  Also returned parts appeared back on the shelves without any sort of inspection from the store. E.g. I found a used oil plug crush ring inserted into a returned pack of 4 crush rings. This should have been an easy thing to spot during the return; as easy as it was for me to spot while shopping.<//review><pics>None</pics>< Response>
None<//Response>

< GmapID>
0x80ec587b7ff3eab5:0x90eeddc874943881<//GmapID>
<Rating>3</Rating>< review>
I want to love Seaside. It has everything I love, mouth watering burritos, one of the best Monte Cristos you've ever had, and glorious thick cut bacon. And this place gives you the biggest portions, so bring your doggy bag and or your appetite.

The one thing to note about this place is there is usually going to be a wait. This is due to the size of the restaurant (90% is outside seating) and that it's a popular place. This alone prevents me from coming here more often, unless I got 3-4 hours to kill.

The reason why I didn't give this a higher rating is the times I do come here, something is always wrong with my order. Normally, if my order is wrong, I'd be more than happy to tell someone but since it takes so long to get my food in the first place, it would probably take another 20 minutes before I'd get it back. And I would feel bad about asking (I know I'm weird). So instead of being a pain for them. I just avoid coming here. But by all means, you should give this place a try, it's definitely a local favorite.< /review>

Mind you, our dog is over 16 years old, blind and deaf. He's a cute little thing, but this concerned us greatly. And we were in desperate need to get him to a vet. He is a terrific vet. <user_id>110545935884204013557<//user_id><text>We randomly walked in for a tattoo and piercing and they were fantastic!!!</text></record>
</dataset><record>
< Text>
As a recent college graduate from UC Santa Cruz, I was really missing the beach towns and art vibes of the city so I decided to spend the weekend in Laguna! It was my first time here and I wanted to get a memento to remember the trip.
Some of the locals suggested Cast of Crowns, and the first thing I noticed was how insanely beautiful the place is. There was a large deck with an ocean view to hang out on, and I was surrounded by gorgeous paintings from the bevy of in-house artists.
Ciera was the piercer on hand, and she was by far the most comforting yet professional body art practitioner I've ever had the pleasure of meeting! She was super bubbly and made me even more excited to be there. We went over what I wanted, a simple nostril stud, and then she painstakingly helped my indecisive self pick out the perfect piece of jewelry. She answered any questions i had about the pieces with absolute ease. This girl is a straight up expert in the field.
After we had everything picked out and cleaned up, we were ready to get started! Ciera walked me through each step of the piercing, making sure I felt comfortable all along the way. The piercing itself was an absolute breeze!! Within the span of a couple deep breaths I was the proud owner of a brand new nostril piercing! Ciera got my nose all cleaned up and gave me a super detailed explanation of what to expect throughout the healing process, then we had a fun little photoshoot out on the deck so she could document the piercing.
This was by far the best experience I've had in a tattoo/piercing shop. Even though I don't live in Laguna, this place is my new regular stop whenever I want to get adorned with some new body art.<//Text>

<rating>4</rating><text>My first time there and went with a friend. Place is a little pricey, $13 talking about splitting a pastrami sandwich but it's a lot of meat and it's very thinly shaved. Unlike the hat and many other restaurants that seem to have good pastrami but just a little on the chewier side this is very thinly sliced and wasn't chewy at all. Probably one of the better pastrami sandwiches I've ever had. Just comes on a simple roll with mustard and pickles. I noticed everybody around me was eating fried zucchini fries as they refer to them which are the thinner zucchini like a french fry that are crispy all the way through not soggy on the inside. I decided to go for onion rings which were good but I've definitely had better. But they were tasty.  Saw they do fries, sweet potato fries, fried mushrooms. They also have a milkshake and ice cream bar ready to make you a Sundae.< /text>< Pictures>

< Review>
It's a great place for small groups. It's also good for just families. We usually order a large sampler (fries, onion rings, fried zucchini, fried mushrooms), which is enough for the four of us and then a burger. Overall a great family dining experience.
1. Portions are very large and satisfying. Though it may seem pricey, each order is large enough for two meals.
2. This is a diner atmosphere so don't expect much more than that. However, the vintage memorabilia add to the ambiance.
3. Staff have always been friendly and helpful.
4. Parking has never been a problem for me, but I haven't been there at peak hours.<//Review>

<review>Ever meet someone who is always with whatever is the hot in "thing" but you still dont want to be around them?

Thats kinda what I feel about Legends Classic Diner

Its amazing how you put a bunch of crap on the walls and people get all "jazzed" about a theme.

The real theme of this place is deep fried not that great food.

I have been here more times then I like to recall because it took quite a few times to convince people that this place just isn't good.

I will say that nothing is horrible. Just nothing stands out at all and considering how much fat is in everything and the fact I can bump into a Greek burger place with my eyes closed.

Almost everything deep fried is overcooked and dry. The food is also just bland.

Feel free to come here just dont come crying to me about it.</review>< pics>
